OL,3,CDrought declared in Yorkshire after
OL,4,Cdriest spring in 132 years
OL,6,FA drought has been declared in
OL,7,FYorkshire following the driest spring
OL,8,Fsince 1893.
OL,10,FThe Environment Agency announced the
OL,11,Fchange in status after declining river
OL,12,Fflows and groundwater levels following
OL,13,Fdry weather in March, April and May.
OL,15,FYorkshire last experienced a drought
OL,16,Fin 2022, when a hosepipe ban was also
OL,17,Fput in place.
