OL,6,FDuring drought conditions the
OL,7,FEnvironment Agency is responsible for
OL,8,Fmaking sure that those abstracting
OL,9,Fwater are not taking more than they
OL,10,Fare licensed to, moving water
OL,11,Fdepending on the needs of agriculture
OL,12,Fand industry and helping to safeguard
OL,13,Ffish, other wildlife and habitat.
OL,15,FIt provides support packages for
OL,16,Ffarmers affected by drought, for
OL,17,Fexample by trading water between
OL,18,Ffarmers to help reduce usage.
OL,20,FDuring a drought the public is
OL,21,Fencouraged to use less water,
