OL,4,Cdriest spring in 132 years
OL,6,FDave Kaye, of Yorkshire Water, said:
OL,7,F"We've seen water demand decrease in
OL,8,Frecent weeks thanks to the welcome
OL,9,Frainfall and the efforts of our
OL,10,Fcustomers to save water.
OL,12,F"We had one of the driest springs on
OL,13,Frecord, which has impacted our
OL,14,Freservoir levels, meaning they are
OL,15,Fmuch lower than normal for this time
OL,16,Fof year. Without significant rainfall
OL,17,Fin the coming months, temporary usage
OL,18,Frestrictions are a possibility.
